    "attributes": {
        "action": "Expand The Dogs (Fouling of Land) Act 1996 To Cover All Animals.",
        "additional_details": "This petition proposes that the Act be expanded from dogs to include all animals where a person who is in charge fails to remove the faeces from the land forthwith.\r\n\r\nReferences:\r\nThe Dogs (Fouling of Land) Act 1996 \r\nClean Neighbourhoods and Environment Act 2005",
        "background": "In 1996 The Dogs (Fouling of Land) Act was introduced into the UK as an Act of the Parliament. The Act was created to make it a criminal offence if a dog fouls at any time on designated land and a person who is in charge of the dog at that time fails to remove the faeces from the land forthwith.",
